              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SPECT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                " Quasi-monoenergetic neutrons.",
                " Energy resolution of the source is estimated to",
                " be 150-200 keV because of deuteron energy spread and",
                " target pressure."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "nuclide": "3-LI-6",
                "field_identifier": "ENR",
                "value": 0.905
              },
              "free_text": [
                "",
                "All samples were prepared on 0.10 mm thick tantalum",
                "backings of 48 mm diameter.",
                "Lithium fluoride (6LiF) samples enriched (90.5 %) in",
                "6Li, with varying thicknesses -",
                "I.   272.9 mug/cm2 for forward direction,",
                "II.  233.5 mug/cm2 for backward direction,",
                "III. 105.3 mug/cm2 for foreground measurement at",
                " forward and backward direction,",
                "IV.  46.0 mug/cm2 for foreground measurement at",
                " forward and backward direction.",
                " 238U(3)O(8) 475.0 mug/cm2 thickness - for neutron flux",
                " measurement.",
                " Ta sample for background measurement."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "PART-DET": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "A",
                "T"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Detection of the number of alpha particles,",
                "tritons, and combined alpha-triton events.",
                "The total yield of charged particles from the",
                "6Li(n,t)4He reaction was obtained as the sum of the",
                "three identified event groups."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                ". Alpha sources were used for energy calibration.",
                ".  Six measurement series :",
                " Series Collimator Working gas pressure Sample",
                " 1      Yes         0.7 atm             I, II",
                " 2      Yes         4.0 atm             I, II",
                " 3      No         1.0 atm              III, IV",
                " 4      No         1.0 atm              III, IV",
                " 5      No         4.0 atm              III, IV",
                " 6      No         4.0 atm              III, IV",
                "Altogether there were 12 measurements (6 series x",
                "2 configurations of samples).",
                ". Determination of the number of detected alpha",
                "particles, tritons, and combined alpha-triton events",
                "were done."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "IOCH"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Gridded ionization chamber filled with gas",
                " (Kr + 3% CO(2)) at variable pressure ( 0.7, 1.0,",
                " 4.0 atm)",
                " For neutron flux monitoring  - two high-purity",
                " (99.999%) 238U(3)O(8) samples of 475.0 mug/cm2",
                " thickness placed inside the ionization chamber.",
                " Anode and cathode signals from the IOCH were",
                " processed by a Pixie-16 digital data acquisition",
                " system (14-bit resolution,250 MHz sampling rate)",
                " consisting of a PXI-6023 XIA-14 chassis (Wiener),",
                " NI PXI-8820 embedded controller, Pixie-16 high-speed",
